C8H6DjlCf0pRKfoVJYSkc5X-4Dc">https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.1995.53.439</a>.=0D=
<br>-----------------------------------------------------------------------=
-----------------------------=0D<br>Abstract=0D<br>-------=0D<br>"Neurocyst=
icercosis cases were identified in 1991 in an Orthodox<br>Jewish community.=
 Transmission was linked to tapeworm-infected<br>immigrant housekeepers fro=
m countries where _Taenia solium_ is<br>endemic. To evaluate the extent of =
and risks for locally acquired<br>cysticercosis, a seroprevalence survey wa=
s conducted in 9% of the<br>households in this community. Cysticercosis ant=
ibodies were detected<br>in 23 (1.3%) of 1789 persons from 612 families. Al=
l 23 seropositive<br>persons were asymptomatic, and no intracerebral lesion=
s were found for<br>the 21 seropositive persons who underwent brain imaging=
.<br>Seropositivity was associated with female sex (relative risk [RR] =3D<=
br>2.45, P =3D 0.049), hiring a domestic worker for childcare duties (RR =
=3D<br>3.79, P =3D 0.05), and with employees from Central America (RR =3D 2=
.70, P<br>=3D 0.0001). Exposure to _T. solium_ in this community is unexpec=
tedly<br>high. Widespread employment of domestic workers from endemic regio=
ns<br>and high employee turnover contributes to exposure risk."=0D<br>=0D<b=
r>A similar study in the schoolchildren could reveal more asymptomatic<br>c=
ases. Three cases in one school in a non-endemic area certainly<br>suggests=
 that a food preparer, probably in the school, carrying adult<br>_T. solium=
_ was the source, but the transmission could certainly have<br>occurred sub=
stantially before the diagnoses were made. - Mod.LL=0D<br>=0D<br>The questi=
on of whether western European countries are actually free<br>of pork tapew=
orms is an interesting one. From the standpoint of<br>commercial swine herd=
s the answer is likely yes. However, feral swine<br>are another matter. Any=
 swine with access to their external<br>environment would also be at signif=
icant risk, especially in areas<br>with feral swine. As proposed in this ar=
ticle<br>(<a href=3D"https://u19268662.ct.sendgrid.net/ss/c/TLh_csrC34X_iXp=
